A tragic plane crash in Greece claimed the lives of all 121 passengers and crew members on board a Helios Airways flight.
Angry relatives confronted airline officials at Larnaca airport, blaming a possible technical fault for the disaster.
Experts suggested a lack of oxygen may have incapacitated the crew, leading to the crash.
The aircraft's decompression issues raised concerns, with past incidents involving similar problems.
Emergency responders recovered black boxes for investigation as authorities ruled out terrorism.
The aviation community mourned the loss and emphasized the need for enhanced safety measures in European skies.
